         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="zoor0310.translation" corresp="#zoor0310.transcription">
            <p>One (is) the God, the Lord of all. Monument of Olefos, (son) of Solemos, who died
                    having a good [name...]</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The inscription does not preserve a date, but it has been dated to the 2nd half of the fifth century CE on the strength of other factors. The tombstone is rectangular, but the lower portion is missing. The text is engraved between incised guide-lines. An outlined cross is engraved above the text, though it has largely faded away. The cross as well as lines 2, 4, and 5 of the inscription preserve red paint. Approximately four lines of text have been lost. The author notes that both names appear elsewhere at Ghor es-Safi.</p>
         </div>
